==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: manipulative
<hw>ma*nip"u*la*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Of or pertaining to manipulation; performed by
manipulation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Prone to attempt to influence others by devious or
subtle psychological means, in order to induce them to do what one
wants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>manipulative</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: manipulative
<hw>ma*nip"u*la*tive</hw>
<pr>(m⟦adot⟧*n⟦icr⟧p"⟦usl⟧*l⟦adot⟧*t⟦icr⟧v)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Education)</fld> <def>Any object given to children to encourage
them to learn by manipulating physical objects; applied especially to
solid objects of varying geometrical shape that can be fit together to
form larger aggregates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manipulator</ent>⟦br⟧
